<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Cortaderia</i> <i>jubata</i> or <i>Cortaderia</i> <i>selloana</i> is dominant in the herbaceous and shrub canopies. Emergent trees and shrubs may be present at low cover. </div>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Herbs < 4 m; cover is open to continuous. </div>
</div>

        
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Membership Rules</h4>
	<ul class="text">
		
		<li><i>Cortaderia jubata</i> or <i>C. selloana</i> > 80% relative cover in the shrub or herbaceous layer (NatureServe 2007).</li>
		
		<li><i>Cortaderia jubata</i> or <i>Cortaderia selloana</i> > 50% relative cover in naturalized stands, or other non-native plants such as <i>Echium candicans</i> > 50% relative cover, or > 30% relative cover with <i>Cortaderia jubata</i> (Buck-Diaz et al. 2021, Sikes et al. 2021).</li>
		
	</ul>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Coastal land, disturbed areas, estuaries, grasslands, urban areas, wetlands.  </div>
</div>

        
